About 120, I should probably let someone who completed it this semester talk about it... but I late dropped 120 this semester after the first midterm, I didn't think it was easy this semester at all, and I stayed in the Piazza and damn the exam distributions were really bad.. From what I've heard from friends who stayed in the class, I don't think this semester (with Jaijeet) it was a light class.

Not sure on 176 and 126, but I've taken 120, 170, and 127

120: Has the lowest workload out of all of them. Probably 8 short-medium length homeworks and 5-6 Python labs on convolution and sampling (which are very easy). The concepts aren't fundamentally hard at all since it is a math class about Fourier Transform and Sampling (which is essentially if you want to anything EE related). This class isn't really a pset based class in my opinion. Take with with Babak if you can. 

170: Workload is really just 1 problem set a week meaning most of your grade is in Midterms and Finals similar to CS70. The homework isn't terribly long (5-6 questions) but they are really really challenging and difficult, which means it takes a lot of time. The difficulty of this class really varies from person to person depending how strong you are in 61B and 70. I found the class bonkers hard conceptually and combined with me enjoying EE over CS, I just pretty much relied on my friends to carry me in homeworks and review sessions in this class to scrap by. 

127: Similar to 170, workload is really just 1 problem set a week. The homework this semester was only 5 problems with subparts but they are really hard as well. Combined with Venkat being a sub-par teacher, the homework can take 10-20 hours because you are own your own to learn the material. Conceptually, I found it not as challenging as 170 because it relied a lot of linear algebra and transforming problems into different optimisation problems. I got a B+ googling my way out of homeworks and my understanding before midterms. 

TLDR: 

Workload: 170 >= 127 >>>>>> 120
Difficulty: 170 >>> 127 >>>>> 120

Taken 176 and 170

170: Agree with everything Anonymous Poet said in terms of workload. Weekly psets, 5-6 questions, but are quite hard conceptually.

176: Psets due every 2 weeks (6 total) with 1 drop. Difficulty about on par or slightly easier than 170, but, now you have 2x the time to solve the problems. In addition, the TAs are super helpful during OH, so you should have no trouble doing the psets. In addition, the class is only ~60 students, so the TAs are available during OH/HW party, unlike all the giant CS upperdivs, where I had to sometimes wait hours to be helped in OH.
